.TH "genpd_power_off" 9 "genpd_power_off" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
genpd_power_off \- Remove power from a given PM domain.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" genpd_power_off
.BI "(struct generic_pm_domain *genpd "  ","
.BI "bool one_dev_on "  ","
.BI "unsigned int depth "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "genpd" 12
PM domain to power down.
.IP "one_dev_on" 12
If invoked from genpd's ->runtime_suspend|\fBresume\fP callback, the
RPM status of the releated device is in an intermediate state, not yet turned
into RPM_SUSPENDED. This means \fBgenpd_power_off\fP must allow one device to not
be RPM_SUSPENDED, while it tries to power off the PM domain.
.IP "depth" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If all of the \fIgenpd\fP's devices have been suspended and all of its subdomains
have been powered down, remove power from \fIgenpd\fP.
